A two-circle Venn diagram with overlapping and non-overlapping areas:
Similarities (overlap): both have an outer shell and inner central layer;
Differences: Earth’s core is metal and solid/liquid, egg yolk is organic and liquid; Earth’s mantle is semi-solid rock, egg white is protein gel.

Need to know: temperature and pressure conditions at each layer;
Excitement: discovering what the inner core looks like;
Worry: extreme heat and crushing pressure might damage equipment;
Preparation step: design heat- and pressure-resistant drilling equipment and protective gear.
